{"TopicId":57564,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Sun Spots in KSP!!!","CreatedByName":"AlamoVampire","CreatedById":78020,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-24T05:22:26Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"AlamoVampire","CreatedById":78020,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-24T05:22:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI was checking on my satellite orbiting the sun, and I noticed something peculiar when I turned my camera towards the sun. Did you know that you can see sunspots on the sun in game? check this out, to either side of the solar disk depending on which picture you look at, either right or left edge of the disk. enjoy \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imageshack.us/photo/my-images/600/hqn0.png/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://imageshack.us/scaled/large/600/hqn0.png\u0022 alt=\u0022hqn0.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imageshack.us/photo/my-images/856/5dy1.png/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://imageshack.us/scaled/large/856/5dy1.png\u0022 alt=\u00225dy1.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gojira","CreatedById":10884,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-24T05:44:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EUnfortunately, they are not procedural but are part of the sun\u0027s model, and as such stay the same throughout the course of your game, no matter how many trillions of years pass.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AlamoVampire","CreatedById":78020,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-24T05:51:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Edoesnt matter if they change or stay the same, the fact that they are there on the Sun, is what impressed me \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SRV Ron","CreatedById":69806,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-24T12:03:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIndeed, very interesting until you get too close.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/q6DqCF4.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022q6DqCF4.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/mlb1m7J.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022mlb1m7J.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Commissioner Tadpole","CreatedById":91993,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-24T13:18:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWell, this has been there since .17.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-12-24T19:56:44Z\u0022 title=\u002212/24/2013 07:56  PM\u0022 data-short=\u002210 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 24, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by Commissioner Tadpole\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LameLefty","CreatedById":57336,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-24T14:47:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Commissioner Tadpole\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Commissioner Tadpole\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003ESorry to burst your bubble, but it has been there since .17.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhy is it \u0022bursting his bubble?\u0022 He didn\u0027t claim it was a new feature, he said it was something he had discovered and was sharing his enjoyment.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Commissioner Tadpole","CreatedById":91993,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-24T19:55:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LameLefty\u0022 data-cite=\u0022LameLefty\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EWhy is it \u0022bursting his bubble?\u0022 He didn\u0027t claim it was a new feature, he said it was something he had discovered and was sharing his enjoyment.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHuh, sorry, I misunderstood.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFixing.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}